tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE wind_turbine_maintenance_schedule (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_cost DECIMAL(10,2),
    completed BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE WindTurbine (
    turbine_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    last_maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_interval INTERVAL,
    energy_production FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE WindTurbineMaintenanceSchedule (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  turbine_id INT,
  maintenance_date DATE,
  maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
  technician_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE Turbines (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  location_id INT,
  model VARCHAR(50),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
  commission_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE WindTurbines (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  location VARCHAR(255),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  installation_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceSchedule (
  schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  turbine_id INT,
  schedule_date DATE,
  maintenance_type VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceLogs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  schedule_id INT,
  log_date DATE,
  technician VARCHAR(255),
  details TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE EnergyProduction (
  production_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  turbine_id INT,
  production_date DATE,
  energy_output DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceSchedule (
    schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    scheduled_date DATE,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(255),
    status VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceRecord (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    schedule_id INT,
    maintenance_date DATE,
    labor_hours DECIMAL(10,2),
    parts_cost DECIMAL(10,2)
);
